Investment Highlights:
  • High Debt Service Coverage Ration (”DSCR”) – Projected 2.3 DSCR on net income indicates a strong financial health, and lower probability of default.
  • 1st Position Notes – Private Lenders will always maintain a 1st position lien on all properties. The highest level of title/lender’s insurance will be purchased on each property.
  • Dedicated in-house property management team.
  • Concentration: We know the Sedona market intimately, and are building out multiple vacation rentals in the city. This allows us to share infrastructure, cross-market, and deliver a great host experience.
  • Extensive deal analysis and structuring experience. Members of our team have bought and sold more then $100MM in residential and commercial properties over the last 15 years.

Property Description

Show stopping Red Rock Vistas in all directions from this dramatic hillside lot just steps away from all the amenities in highly desirable Uptown Sedona.

Located in a prime Sedona neighborhood with no HOA, this location is close to forest trails, charming galleries and shops, and popular restaurants.

Property Highlights:
  • Approx 1/3 acre with City sewer, natural gas, electricity and water available

  • Rare uptown vacant lot. Central and private.
  • Unimpeded views of Cathedral Rock, Snoopy, Thunder Mountain, Wilson Mountain and Elephant Rock
  • Guest home permitted, which allows for room to build two STR units.
  • No HOA which removes risk of STR limitations being imposed in the futue.
  • High-end neighborhood.

Development Overview

Zomes Development is in contract on the land, and has contracted with Shell Dwellings, LLC to be build a 1 bedroom Zome (700 sqft), and 2 bedroom Zome (1000 sqft).

Construction is set to begin mid April, and be completed by mid July.

Development Highlights:
  • The two units will sleep 4 and 6 guests respectively.

  • Dual-zone hot tub and lap pool for each unit.

  • Big investment in outdoor living room and dining room useable for four seasons.
  • Smart glass, HVAC units, and Radiant floor heating for a comfortable stay in all weather.
  • Site layout design ensure each unit has visual and sound privacy, but can also be rented together for larger groups.
  • Modular construction means units will go up fast with no risk of material or labor cost over run.
  • High end finishes and furnishing(Take a tour)

Key Investment Risks

We have a limited operating history. As a result, an investment in one of our properties entails more risk than an investment in a company with a substantial operating history.

In addition, our ability to successfully operate our business and implement our operating policies and investment strategy depends on many factors, including:

  • - Our ability to obtain the additional capital
  • - Our ability to effectively manage renovation, maintenance, marketing and other operating costs for our properties
  • - Economic conditions in our markets, including changes in employment and household earnings and expenses, as well as the condition of the financial and real estate markets and the economy, in general
  • - Our ability to maintain high occupancy rates and target rent levels
  • - Costs that are beyond our control, including title litigation, litigation with guests, legal compliance, real estate taxes, HOA fees and insurance;
  • - Judicial and regulatory developments affecting landlord-guest relations that may affect or delay our ability increase rental rates
  • - Reversal of population, employment or homeownership trends in our markets
  • - Interest rate levels and volatility, such as the accessibility of short-term and long-term financing on desirable terms
